commit.message: Update .travis.yml
Extend the equality condition to match both xml_attrs an data instead of data only
Bump the version number for future development.
Updated CHANGES and RELEASENOTES files for v1.0.1.
Release version 1.0.1.
Add the emit_xml() function to the README file.

Add top-level emit_xml() function (#11)

* Add top-level emit_xml() function to resolve Juniper/jxmlease#9.
Add documentation and test cases.
Redo the logic in emit_handler to split detection of when it is *permissible* to use the full_document option from the detection of when we should *default* to using it.

* Quelch documentation warnings by preventing Sphinx from guessing (incorrectly) at the cross reference for (list) and (dict) argument types.

* Revert commit 6c07d0c and replace it with a better fix suggested by @stacywsmith

* In the emit_xml() function, do not suppress exceptions that occur during object conversion.
Change requested by @stacywsmith.

Fix error detection when processing an XML document. (#8)

- If the document is empty, it will return an empty dictionary (or no matches, in the case of a generator).
- If the document contains malformed content, it should now return an exception.

Also, added test cases for this.

This resolves Juniper/jxmlease#7.
Bumping version number for continued development on the master branch.
Changes to support building of PyPI packages.
Switch the README file to restructured text.
Release 1.0
Documentation updates.
Bring in changes from the development branch.

Add tests and update documentation for the find_nodes_with_tag() and has_node_with_tag() methods.
Note that this makes a small change in the behavior of these methods: when running a recursive search, they will continue searching children of matching nodes.
Delete code specific for supporting Python version <= 2.5.

Reorganize package and get rid of meta-classes

- Convert the jxmlease module into a package with multiple modules.
  We don't really need multiple modules, but it will be nice to have the code broken up
  into multiple files. This breakup requires a little hack to delay the resolution of some
  symbols until all the code has been loaded.
- Freedom from metaclasses!
  This commit gets rid of the metaclass and replaces everything the metaclass used to
  do with standard mechanisms.
  This also now implements the `super()` calls for `__new__()` and `__init__()` methods,
  allowing for more standard subclassing.
- General cleanup
  - Add some docstrings.
  - Cleanup some nits highlighted by pylint.
  - Silence some pylint false alarms.
  - Add `__all__` variables to all modules.
  - Modify the way docstrings are auto-generated (first step to removing the meta-class).
  - Fix some more pylint nits
  - Customize pylint:
    - Tell pylint about variable names we consider "good".
    - Tell pylint to follow the PEP-8 naming convention, even if it thinks (sometimes
      inaccurately) that the variable is constant.
    - Enable more checks.

Updating installation documentation

More accurately reflect the prerequisites information.
Updating installation documentation per discussion with Jonathan.

Merge pull request #4 from jonlooney/master

Make ElementTree a required prerequisite.
Add an __all__ variable to limit what is imported by a wildcard import.

Make ElementTree a required prerequisite.
Because it is part of the standard library, this should be irrelevant for any Python >= 2.5.

Correct some errors spotted by (or inspired by) pylint

Also, correct some typos and commit the pylintrc file.

Correct some errors spotted by pylint, or noticed while reviewing the pylint results.
Also, commit the pylintrc file.
Correct some typos.
Adding lines that PyPI requires when README is using markdown.

Updating the install instructions to indicate minimum version is
Python 2.6, not Python 2.5.
